<i>Don't worry, Hye-ryeong.</i>

128
00:13:33,323 --> 00:13:35,492
I checked that
the hall director wasn't in her office.

129
00:13:35,617 --> 00:13:37,911
<i>After roll-call, in room 207,</i>

130
00:13:37,995 --> 00:13:41,456
<i>Yeo Jeong-min, Ko Hye-ryeong,
Yoon Seol-hui, and Eun Yeong-ro</i>

131
00:13:41,540 --> 00:13:44,626
<i>ate</i> ramyeon <i>and chat with Lee Jang-hui
from room 209</i>

132
00:13:44,710 --> 00:13:47,129
<i>and Kim Gang-hui and Lim So-yeon
from room 206.</i>

133
00:13:47,212 --> 00:13:50,340
<i>Yeong-ro received a necklace as a gift
from an unnamed man who was</i>

134
00:13:50,424 --> 00:13:51,925
<i>her partner at the Open House.</i>

135
00:13:52,384 --> 00:13:53,969
<i>They must be seeing each other.</i>

136
00:13:54,720 --> 00:13:56,346
The girl who treated me?

137
00:13:57,389 --> 00:14:01,059
<i>I heard the ANSP director's son is dead.
What if they try to retaliate against us?</i>

138
00:14:06,565 --> 00:14:08,233
<i>Did you forget about the instructions?</i>

139
00:14:09,151 --> 00:14:11,695
But they were given before his death.

140
00:14:12,070 --> 00:14:15,365
<i>I'm at Hosu University where
the armed spies are holding people hostage</i>

141
00:14:15,449 --> 00:14:18,285
<i>after escaping the ANSP surveillance.</i>

142
00:14:18,368 --> 00:14:20,162
<i>The university is closed to the public</i>

143
00:14:20,245 --> 00:14:23,498
<i>including its students, and the police
special forces have been sent in.</i>

144
00:14:23,582 --> 00:14:28,045
<i>ANSP has camped in front of the dorm
and taken control of the scene--</i>

145
00:14:31,173 --> 00:14:34,885
Set a booby trap on the cafeteria windows
and put an extra bomb.

146
00:14:35,969 --> 00:14:37,888
<i>A bomb?</i>

147
00:14:38,263 --> 00:14:40,682
If they try to deceive us again,

148
00:14:43,268 --> 00:14:44,519
I'll push the button.

149
00:16:05,308 --> 00:16:07,853
Talk about bad timing.

150
00:16:08,562 --> 00:16:10,230
If only you'd come in a bit later.

151
00:16:11,773 --> 00:16:12,816
Turn around.

152
00:16:39,051 --> 00:16:40,177
That…

153
00:16:40,844 --> 00:16:42,846
Why is that…

154
00:17:01,198 --> 00:17:03,366
You know I have
a detonator in my pocket, right?

155
00:17:04,076 --> 00:17:05,994
Don't try anything funny.

156
00:17:06,870 --> 00:17:08,330
Will you blow everyone up?

157
00:17:09,414 --> 00:17:12,834
You know Lee Seong-jo, right? The one
who came to assassinate the president.

158
00:17:13,919 --> 00:17:17,172
He fell in love with someone in the South
and is living happily.

159
00:17:19,299 --> 00:17:22,427
Don't you want to live here
with someone you love, like him?

160
00:17:28,391 --> 00:17:31,269
If you want to live happily
with that woman, don't do anything stupid.

161
00:17:32,104 --> 00:17:33,313
I won't let it slide twice.

162
00:17:34,815 --> 00:17:36,942
"That woman"? Who?

163
00:17:38,276 --> 00:17:42,906
Oh, her? She's just
one of my subordinates. Nothing more.

164
00:17:43,740 --> 00:17:45,450
Just colleagues.

165
00:18:01,174 --> 00:18:02,259
Go in.

166
00:18:30,495 --> 00:18:31,705
How is she?

167
00:18:31,788 --> 00:18:34,124
I gave her a tranquilizer,

168
00:18:34,207 --> 00:18:36,793
so she'll be fine after some sleep.

169
00:18:49,014 --> 00:18:50,724
Can we have a word for a minute?

170
00:19:14,873 --> 00:19:16,750
I know the North and the South
made a deal,

171
00:19:16,833 --> 00:19:18,501
but we never know

172
00:19:19,044 --> 00:19:21,379
how things will turn out and when.

173
00:19:23,048 --> 00:19:24,299
You know that, right?

174
00:19:25,759 --> 00:19:26,801
Of course, ma'am.

175
00:19:26,885 --> 00:19:28,678
So the ANSP director's daughter…

176
00:19:31,806 --> 00:19:34,100
hid you in this dorm?

177
00:19:35,727 --> 00:19:36,770
Yes.

178
00:19:40,482 --> 00:19:44,194
Since you're indebted to her, it must
be bothering you. I understand that.

179
00:19:46,404 --> 00:19:50,116
But don't let
your personal feelings ruin our mission.

180
00:19:54,120 --> 00:19:56,665
I never had any personal feelings for her.

181
00:19:59,751 --> 00:20:01,378
I'm relieved to hear that.

182
00:20:11,388 --> 00:20:14,182
The hostage situation
hadn't been in the news all this time,

183
00:20:14,266 --> 00:20:16,142
but the news about it just broke out.

184
00:20:16,601 --> 00:20:18,311
And my face has been disclosed.

185
00:20:19,437 --> 00:20:23,108
Will we really be able
to go back alive in ten days?

186
00:20:25,986 --> 00:20:27,237
Comrade Lim Soo-ho.

187
00:20:28,571 --> 00:20:31,241
Are you worried about that
or doubting the party?

188
00:20:31,324 --> 00:20:33,451
I'm not doubting the party's orders.

189
00:20:34,202 --> 00:20:35,996
I just don't trust the ANSP.

190
00:20:36,579 --> 00:20:37,831
As I told you,

191
00:20:38,873 --> 00:20:41,793
last time we followed
the instructions and went out there,

192
00:20:41,876 --> 00:20:44,337
they sprayed us with bullets to kill us.

193
00:20:46,631 --> 00:20:50,093
If what you're saying is true, it means
they stabbed the party in the back.

194
00:20:50,176 --> 00:20:51,970
Would the party really have

195
00:20:52,762 --> 00:20:55,181
negotiated with such backstabbers again?

196
00:20:57,559 --> 00:20:58,476
Then…

197
00:21:00,520 --> 00:21:01,855
let me ask you one thing.

198
00:21:07,569 --> 00:21:09,070
Why in ten days?

199
00:21:10,780 --> 00:21:11,990
You seriously don't know?

200
00:21:12,866 --> 00:21:16,494
A veteran spy like you who's been
acting in covert all over Germany?

201
00:21:56,034 --> 00:21:57,160
That's a bomb, isn't it?

202
00:21:57,744 --> 00:22:01,873
They said they'd release more of us,
but aren't they going to just kill us all?

203
00:22:01,956 --> 00:22:04,292
There you go again.
Don't jump to conclusions.

204
00:22:04,876 --> 00:22:07,337
They wouldn't dare.
The army is surrounding this place.

205
00:22:09,422 --> 00:22:12,175
Wait. Where's Yeong-ro?

206
00:22:12,258 --> 00:22:14,677
What if they took only her somewhere safe?

207
00:22:15,178 --> 00:22:16,096
Keep it down.

208
00:22:16,179 --> 00:22:19,182
He took her out of here in secret.

209
00:22:19,766 --> 00:22:21,309
Stop talking nonsense.

210
00:22:23,353 --> 00:22:24,479
Get back to sleep.

211
00:22:24,854 --> 00:22:27,565
Even when they tried
to kill the doctor by the window,

212
00:22:27,649 --> 00:22:30,193
he desperately tried
to save Yeong-ro first.

213
00:22:30,276 --> 00:22:31,611
I saw it with my own eyes!

214
00:22:31,694 --> 00:22:32,821
Gye Bun-ok.

215
00:22:34,739 --> 00:22:36,699
I bet even if all of us here are killed,

216
00:22:36,783 --> 00:22:38,993
he'll still try to save Yeong-ro.

217
00:22:40,161 --> 00:22:41,579
It's already been two hours.

218
00:22:42,664 --> 00:22:44,165
They must've released her. Right?

219
00:22:44,249 --> 00:22:45,375
Of course not.

220
00:22:48,378 --> 00:22:49,879
She passed out.

221
00:22:50,547 --> 00:22:54,217
After hearing that her brother died during
an engagement with a Northern spy boat.

222
00:22:55,176 --> 00:22:56,636
Her brother died?

223
00:22:56,970 --> 00:22:58,513
I feel so bad for her.

224
00:22:58,596 --> 00:23:01,266
-Oh, no.
-Poor Yeong-ro.

225
00:23:13,194 --> 00:23:14,112
Honey.

226
00:23:14,195 --> 00:23:17,115
What are you doing here?
The guests are coming.

227
00:23:18,616 --> 00:23:20,118
It's all my fault.

228
00:23:21,202 --> 00:23:23,496
I'm the one who got him killed.

229
00:23:25,707 --> 00:23:27,959
That's not your fault.

230
00:23:28,543 --> 00:23:30,879
When you sent him to the front lines,

231
00:23:30,962 --> 00:23:34,757
you were in a crisis because of the Campus
Stabilization Act. You had no choice.

232
00:23:35,467 --> 00:23:37,802
On top of that, he protested
against the government.

233
00:23:37,886 --> 00:23:39,971
Very enthusiastically, at that.

234
00:23:40,054 --> 00:23:43,558
I was so worried
that you might get on Code 1's bad side.

235
00:23:46,978 --> 00:23:47,896
Honey.

236
00:23:49,063 --> 00:23:51,483
I know it's really hard for you,

237
00:23:51,566 --> 00:23:55,236
but our Yeong-u
bravely sacrificed his life

238
00:23:55,320 --> 00:23:59,407
for our country and people while
fighting against spies from the North.

239
00:24:01,117 --> 00:24:03,328
If only it weren't for Operation Phoenix…

240
00:24:05,455 --> 00:24:06,623
If Code 1 finds out

241
00:24:06,706 --> 00:24:09,334
you blame the operation for it,
you'll be doomed!

242
00:24:09,792 --> 00:24:11,920
Now that the operation has failed,

243
00:24:12,504 --> 00:24:14,005
if you're pushed out,

244
00:24:14,088 --> 00:24:15,215
what about Yeong-ro?

245
00:24:15,298 --> 00:24:17,425
We can't bring Yeong-u back,

246
00:24:17,509 --> 00:24:19,719
but we must save Yeong-ro at all cost!

247
00:24:20,220 --> 00:24:22,347
I know you made a deal with the North,

248
00:24:22,430 --> 00:24:26,851
as long as she's in the hands of
those brutal spies, she can never be safe.

249
00:24:27,435 --> 00:24:29,229
Honey!

250
00:24:30,230 --> 00:24:32,774
You must pull yourself together!

251
00:24:33,441 --> 00:24:35,985
I know. I know that.

252
00:24:36,778 --> 00:24:37,987
Yeong-u…

253
00:24:38,363 --> 00:24:39,864
Yeong-u…

254
00:24:43,952 --> 00:24:45,703
<i>And I'll look out for her</i>

255
00:24:46,204 --> 00:24:48,623
by her side until she becomes an old lady,

256
00:24:49,832 --> 00:24:52,085
so don't worry about a thing, Mom.

257
00:24:52,168 --> 00:24:54,170
I'm just three years younger than you.

258
